# Tool Test
# Exercises run-demo.mjs controls and commands against a live SharePoint site.

[var: SITE = https://microsoft.sharepoint-df.com/teams/ZachDemos/]
[category: Other]

[section: setup]

Checking the site is reachable before running tests.

[assert: ${SITE}]

[section: demo]

# ── Navigation ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

This is a talking point. It should appear in the terminal with an amber bar,
and in the widget's full-mode view below the step name.

Navigate to the demo site to start.

[navigate: ${SITE}]

# ── Pause + Skip test ───────────────────────────────────────────

TRY THIS: Press S (or click Skip in the widget) to skip this pause.
You should jump straight to the next step.

[pause: Skippable pause — try pressing S]

# ── Back test ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

TRY THIS: Press B (or click Back in the widget) to go back to the
skippable pause above and re-run it. Then press Enter to come back here.

[pause: Back test — try pressing B, then Enter twice to continue]

# ── Open chat ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

Opening the Copilot chat pane via the FAB. Tests the open-chat command
and the fallback selector chain.

[open-chat]

# ── Prompt + Wait ───────────────────────────────────────────────

Sending a simple grounding prompt. Watch the slow-typing speed and
the response-detection logic (Stop button → feedback buttons fallback).

[prompt: What is this site about? Give me a one-sentence answer.]

[wait]

Copilot responded. The talking points you see now were set after [wait]
completed — the widget should update to show these lines.

[pause: Confirm the response looks reasonable, then continue]

# ── New chat ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Clearing the conversation with the new-chat command.

[new-chat]

# ── Second prompt ───────────────────────────────────────────────

A second prompt in the fresh conversation tests that new-chat worked and
the input is still reachable after clearing.

[prompt: List the document libraries on this site in a bullet list.]

[wait]

# ── Sleep ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Testing the sleep directive — a 2-second pause with no user input needed.

[sleep: 2s]

# ── Screenshot ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

Saving a screenshot to confirm the file-write path works.

[screenshot: tools/screenshots/tool-test.png]

# ── Finish ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

All steps complete. If you can read this talking point in the widget's
full-mode view, the context mirroring is working correctly.

Press Enter to finish.

[pause: All done]

[section: reset]

This demo is read-only — navigate home to restore the view.

[navigate: ${SITE}]
